.:: Puzzle 2x7-Level-8-2::.
7 different games are played: canasta, backgammon, monopoly, go, billiard, poker, snooker
The people use 7 different means of transport: roller, tram, subway, trike, car, bike, van
 1. the person driving the car is in the middle##1
 2. the person driving the bike is not the person playing monopoly##6
 3. the person driving the subway is not to the left of the person driving the roller##8
 4. the person driving the bike is between the person driving the roller and the person playing monopoly##2
 5. the person playing billiard is in an odd position##4
 6. the person playing canasta is on the right of the person driving the trike##1
 7. the person playing snooker is in an odd position##4
 8. the person driving the subway is not to the left of the person driving the trike##8
 9. the person playing poker is somewhere to the right of the person playing go##5
10. the person driving the trike is on the left of the person driving the subway##1
11. the person playing canasta is on the right of the person playing billiard##1
12. the person driving the tram is not to the right of the person driving the trike##8
13. the person playing go is not to the left of the person playing snooker##8
14. the person driving the trike is somewhere to the right of the person driving the car##5
15. the person playing backgammon is on the left or right of the person driving the trike##3
16. the person playing monopoly is on the left of the person driving the car##1

.:: Answer ::.
|         |    1    |    2    |     3      |    4    |     5      |      6      |      7      |
| Game   | snooker | go | monopoly    | backgammon | billiard | canasta | poker |
| Transport     | roller     | bike   | tram | car | trike       | subway        | van      |

